Originally Answered: What do you really think of a grown man who still reads MAD Magazine and gets a laugh?

I am in my 40s, I bought this book two days ago…

And this one…because I’d get home and it be gone because one of my lovers fell in love with Calvin and Hobbes too…

So for me, I really don’t care what others think if I read these.

Humour I find is for those of high intellect. It is a skill most do not have and did not develop and so is fun too.

It makes me relax, life is serious enough as it is and if a woman got problem with it and calls it childish - that’s my qualifier to know I don’t want her in my life. I like fun and so fun is a big thing for me, to smile, to relax, not feel so bothered about what other people think.

In fact, all my dating books I am writing is in comic form so it’s fun to read and relaxing to read. Even if people won’t apply it to their life, because it takes courage to do it and well, some folks are strong in comfort zone - but… at least they still got something to read and have a laugh.

I see as a way to also just relax, take a break from the world and just enjoy a good laugh. Life is serious as it is. Good to chill and take a break.

So to my Quora followers…here’s Calvin and Hobbes…hope it makes you laugh and smile…

Stay young.

Life doesn’t always have to be all grown up, so serious.

We all got a child in us that’s fun, curious and wants to let go and be free..and…have a laugh at ourselves :)
